FBIS4-43201 "drweu114_q_94006" FBIS-WEU-94-114 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 TURKEY Court Rules To Stop Government Decree Powers Court Rules To Stop Government Decree Powers TA1006195494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 GMT 10 Jun 94 TA1006195494 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report] [Text] The Constitutional Court has ruled to stop the implementation of the law allowing the government to issue law-decrees to make changes in the state organization and personnel regulations. The Motherland Party applied to the Constitutional Court asking it to stop the implementation of the law until the case for its cancellation is concluded. The Constitutional Court discussed the application today and with a majority of votes, ruled to stop the implementation of the law to prevent situations and losses that might be impossible or difficult to recover.
